## ‚úÖ Cancel Axios Request in React (`useEffect`)

This is the **MOST IMPORTANT real‚ÄĎworld case**.

### ‚úÖ Search / Filter API (best practice)

```jsx
import axios from "axios";
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

function Search({ query }) {
  const [results, setResults] = useState([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!query) return;

    const controller = new AbortController();

    axios.get("/api/search", {
      params: { q: query },
      signal: controller.signal
    })
    .then(res => setResults(res.data))
    .catch(err => {
      if (err.name === "CanceledError") {
        console.log("Previous request cancelled");
      }
    });

    // ‚úÖ cancel previous request
    return () => controller.abort();
  }, [query]);

  return <div>{JSON.stringify(results)}</div>;
}
```

### ‚úÖ Why this works

*   When `query` changes ‚Üí effect re‚ÄĎruns
*   React runs **cleanup first**
*   Previous Axios request gets cancelled
*   Only latest request updates the UI ‚úÖ

***

## ‚úÖ Interview Explanation (Short)

> **Axios requests are cancelled using `AbortController` by passing the signal and aborting it during cleanup to prevent race conditions and stale updates.**

