# ‚ö†ÔłŹ Legacy Way (Deprecated): `CancelToken`

ūüö® **DO NOT use in new projects**  
‚ö†ÔłŹ Still asked in interviews (know it!)

***

## ‚ĚĆ Axios CancelToken Example

```js
import axios from "axios";

const source = axios.CancelToken.source();

axios.get("/api/data", {
  cancelToken: source.token
})
.catch(err => {
  if (axios.isCancel(err)) {
    console.log("Cancelled:", err.message);
  }
});

// cancel
source.cancel("Request cancelled");
```

### Why deprecated?

*   Custom implementation
*   Redundant with native `AbortController`
*   Removed from Axios future roadmap

‚úÖ Mention **only for legacy systems**.

